         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Independent Safety Assessor — Cityringen Branch off to Sydhavnen (CWISA)</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="71313410"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>Independent Safety Assessor for the safety assessment of the Civil Works construction comprised by the contract CRSH1 in phase 4 (the construction phase after contract signature) of the project: “CItyringen Branch off to Sydhavnen” (CRSH).</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71311200"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="71317210"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="90711100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="DK01"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>The services shall be performed at the Assessors home office, at Metroselskabets office and at the construction sites.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Cityringen branch off to Sydhavnen (CRSH):</P>
                  <P>The construction of CRSH will be performed via a civil works design and build contract called CRSH1 plus a Transportation system design and build contract CRSH4.</P>
                  <P>The physical connection to Cityringen is performed by the current CWC contractor (CMT) on Cityringen. The supply of rolling stock and high level transportation supplies like ATC and SCADA will be supplied by the current TSC contractor (ASTS) on Cityringen. Finally a number of other contracts like utility relocations, road diversions etc. will be entered separately by the client. By nature the CW contract CRSH will have interfaces to CRH4, CWC at Havneholmen shaft and to TSC.</P>
                  <P>Metroselskabet has already entered into a contract with TÜV Rheinland InterTraffic GmbH with DNV-GL as subcontractor as a System level independent safety assessor (SYSISA) for CR, Cityringen Branch off to Nordhavnen (CRNH) and CRSH.</P>
                  <P>The SYSISA is performing the safety assessment of the CW supplies for CR and CRNH as well as performing the safety assessment of the complete fleet of rolling stock for CR, CRNH and CRSH plus all TS supplies like ATC, SCADA and other TS subsystems for the CR, CRNH and CRSH projects.</P>
                  <P>Services put out to tender:</P>
                  <P>In conclusion the scope of work for the CWISA is the safety assessment of CRSH1.</P>
                  <P>Independent safety assessor will be procured to assess all aspects related to CRSH1 of the specifications, design,manufacture, construction, installation, training, testing, commissioning, trial running and final acceptance of the Transit system to verify compliance with the governing standards for the assessment services and the standards governing safety of Cityringen Branch off to Sydhavnen;</P>
                  <P>— Implement the safety assessment of CRSH1 for the contractual set-up of CRSH,</P>
                  <P>— The CW certification process,</P>
                  <P>— Perform safety assessment of the contractors works including the interface work to CR at the Havneholmen shaft to ensure that the CRSH1 contractors and sub-contractors are following the specified standards,</P>
                  <P>— Interface substantially with the SYSISA by supplying assessment reports and information to SYSISA as well as receiving assessment reports and information from SYSISA,</P>
                  <P>— Participate in meetings to ensure progress and solving technical issues.</P>
                  <P>Fur further information please refer to the tender document "Scope of work".</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
